{"info": {"author": "dmitriym09", "author_email": "dmitriym.09.12.1989@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# py-clamav\n\nLibClamAV ctypes binding\n\n## Install\n\n- install or [download](https://www.clamav.net/downloads) libclamv\n- `pip install py-clamav`\n\n## Using\n\n```python\nimport os\n\nfrom py_clamav import ClamAvScanner\n\nwith ClamAvScanner() as scanner:\n    # scan file by path\n    path_file = 'path/to/file'\n    infected, virname = scanner.scan_file(path_file)\n\n    # scan file by fileno\n    fileno = os.memfd_create('testfile')\n    try:\n        os.write(fileno, b'data')\n        os.lseek(fileno, 0, 0)\n        infected, virname = scanner.scan_fileno(fileno)\n    finally:\n        os.close(fileno)\n```\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/dmitriym09/py-clamav", "keywords": "antivirus,ClamAv,LibClamAV", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "py-clamav", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-clamav/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-clamav/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/dmitriym09/py-clamav"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/py-clamav/1.0.1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.8", "summary": "LibClamAV ctypes binding", "version": "1.0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>py-clamav</h1>\n<p>LibClamAV ctypes binding</p>\n<h2>Install</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>install or <a href=\"https://www.clamav.net/downloads\" rel=\"nofollow\">download</a> libclamv</li>\n<li><code>pip install py-clamav</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Using</h2>\n<pre>